---

<Layout title="Number Theory Ch.1 — Divisibility" favicon="#">
  <main>

    <a href="/reading/number-theory/" class="text-sm mb-4 inline-block">&larr; back to Number Theory</a>

    <h1>Divisibility</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">Jim Hefferon &middot; Elementary Number Theory &middot; <a href="https://jheffero.w3.uvm.edu/numbertheory/">Ch. 1</a></p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none">An integer <strong>a</strong> divides <strong>b</strong> if b = a &middot; k for some integer k. From this single relation flow the division algorithm, the GCD, and the Euclidean algorithm that computes it.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- 1. The divides relation -->
    <h3>The divides relation</h3>
    <p>We write a | b ("a divides b") when there exists an integer k such that b = a k. Divisibility is reflexive (a | a) and transitive (if a | b and b | c then a | c), but not symmetric.</p>

    <!-- SVG: Number line with multiples of 3 highlighted -->
    <div class="flex justify-center my-6">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 440 80" class="w-full max-w-lg" style="font-family: ui-monospace, monospace;">
        <text x="220" y="15" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" font-size="10" fill-opacity="0.35">Multiples of 3 on the number line</text>
        <!-- Number line -->
        <line x1="20" y1="45" x2="420" y2="45" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1" stroke-opacity="0.3"/>
        <!-- Ticks and numbers 0-12 -->
        <line x1="30" y1="40" x2="30" y2="50" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1" stroke-opacity="0.3"/>
        <text x="30" y="65" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" font-size="10" fill-opacity="0.3">0</text>
        <line x1="60" y1="40" x2="60" y2="50" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1" stroke-opacity="0.3"/>
